WEBVTT

1
00:01:26.712 --> 00:01:29.329
<i>There's 100,000 streets in this city.</i>

2
00:01:30.549 --> 00:01:33.211
<i>You don't need to know the route.</i>

3
00:01:33.468 --> 00:01:38.429
<i>You give me a time and a place,
I give you a five-minute window.</i>

4
00:01:38.640 --> 00:01:42.178
Anything happens in that five minutes
and I'm yours.

5
00:01:42.394 --> 00:01:44.476
No matter what.

6
00:01:44.730 --> 00:01:49.566
Anything happens 3 minute either side
of that and you're on your own.

7
00:01:49.776 --> 00:01:51.813
Do you understand?

8
00:01:55.198 --> 00:01:56.688
Good.

9
00:01:59.369 --> 00:02:02.953
And you won't be able to reach me
on this phone again.

10
00:02:34.571 --> 00:02:36.608
Hey, there you are!

11
00:02:36.865 --> 00:02:38.822
She's down there.

12
00:02:39.034 --> 00:02:41.526
Plain Jane boring,
just like you asked for,

13
00:02:41.745 --> 00:02:45.864
but I dropped in 300 horses
on the inside - she is going to fly!

14
00:02:46.750 --> 00:02:49.993
You look like a zombie, kid.
You getting any sleep?

15
00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:54.710
Can I offer you some Benzedrine,
Dexedrine, caffeine, nicotine?

16
00:02:54.925 --> 00:02:58.008
Oh, you don't smoke. That's right.
Better off.

17
00:02:59.262 --> 00:03:01.924
There she is!

18
00:03:02.099 --> 00:03:06.343
Chevy Impala, the most popular car
in the state of California.

19
00:03:07.312 --> 00:03:09.599
No one will be looking at you.

20
00:03:17.781 --> 00:03:20.273
(Distant police sirens)

21
00:03:25.163 --> 00:03:30.078
<i>(Car radio) 19,000 Clipper fans on their
feet here at Staples Center, Los Angeles.</i>

22
00:03:30.293 --> 00:03:32.250
(Commentary continues)

23
00:04:06.830 --> 00:04:08.992
(Gunshot)

24
00:04:10.125 --> 00:04:12.708
(Alarm goes off)

25
00:04:13.754 --> 00:04:15.665
(Police Radio crackles)

26
00:04:17.007 --> 00:04:22.719
<i>(Police radio) - Robert Victor 3...
- License 514, Robert Victor 3...</i>

27
00:04:23.972 --> 00:04:28.261
<i>(Radio) They're making a strong line with
six minutes to go in the fourth quarter...</i>

28
00:04:28.477 --> 00:04:29.477
<i>(Police radio) Copy.</i>

29
00:04:29.728 --> 00:04:33.016
<i>(Radio) ...excitement and celebration
if they win tonight...</i>

30
00:04:33.148 --> 00:04:35.310
(Police radio crackles)

31
00:04:35.525 --> 00:04:39.063
<i>(Police radio) Code 30 ringer located
at 421 South Alameda.</i>

32
00:04:41.406 --> 00:04:43.522
<i>(Police radio) Reports
of shots fired at Code 30.</i>

33
00:04:43.658 --> 00:04:46.446
(Alarm still ringing)

34
00:04:56.713 --> 00:04:58.124
Come on.

35
00:04:59.382 --> 00:05:01.419
Where the fuck is he? Come on.

36
00:05:03.178 --> 00:05:06.011
<i>(Police radio) Unit 5, what's your 20?</i>

37
00:05:06.181 --> 00:05:09.924
<i>(Police radio) We are approximately
two minutes from that location.</i>

38
00:05:14.231 --> 00:05:16.393
(Distant police siren)

39
00:05:16.608 --> 00:05:19.566
Come on, man. Where the hell are you?

40
00:05:23.114 --> 00:05:24.696
Come on!

41
00:05:26.326 --> 00:05:28.033
Come on!

42
00:05:28.161 --> 00:05:30.653
Come on, get in, get in, get in!

43
00:05:31.623 --> 00:05:33.580
Go, go! Go!

44
00:05:36.461 --> 00:05:39.014
<i>(Police radio) All units
be advised. Possible</i>

45
00:05:39.038 --> 00:05:41.672
<i>vehicle in question.
Late model silver Impala.</i>

46
00:05:43.635 --> 00:05:47.094
(Sports commentary continues on radio)

47
00:05:52.060 --> 00:05:54.444
<i>(Radio) Just four
minutes here on the clock</i>

48
00:05:54.468 --> 00:05:56.930
<i>in this make-or-break
game for the Clippers.</i>

49
00:06:02.028 --> 00:06:04.019
(Commentary continues)

50
00:06:09.494 --> 00:06:13.328
<i>(Police radio) 1-Adam-3,
South Bay at Seventh, clear.</i>

51
00:06:15.166 --> 00:06:17.658
<i>(Police radio) Roger, 1-Adam-3.</i>

52
00:06:17.794 --> 00:06:20.912
<i>(Police radio) Requesting air unit support.</i>

53
00:06:21.047 --> 00:06:23.004
<i>(Police radio) Dispatch, I got it.</i>

54
00:06:33.643 --> 00:06:36.977
<i>(Police radio) Unit 5 to Dispatch,
heading eastbound on Sixth.</i>

55
00:06:37.147 --> 00:06:39.184
<i>(Police radio) Copy that, Unit 5.</i>

56
00:06:50.577 --> 00:06:54.616
<i>(Police radio) Base to Air 3.
Any sign of that silver Impala?</i>

57
00:06:55.707 --> 00:06:57.789
<i>(Police radio) Air 3 to Base. Negative.</i>

58
00:07:05.091 --> 00:07:08.049
<i>(Police radio) I have visual heading west
on Seventh Street Bridge.</i>

59
00:07:11.598 --> 00:07:14.556
<i>(Police radio) Copy, Air 3.</i>

60
00:07:38.625 --> 00:07:42.539
<i>(Police radio) Base, Air 3 here.
We've lost visual on suspect.</i>

61
00:07:42.712 --> 00:07:45.420
(Helicopter whirrs overhead)

62
00:07:53.181 --> 00:07:56.299
<i>(Police radio) Base to Air 3.
Possible gang shooting in progress.</i>

63
00:07:56.434 --> 00:07:59.722
<i>(Police radio) Proceed immediately
to Washington and La Brea.</i>

64
00:08:00.021 --> 00:08:02.262
<i>(Police radio) Roger, Dispatch. I'm out.</i>

65
00:08:17.080 --> 00:08:19.196
<i>(Police radio) All
westbound units be advised,</i>

66
00:08:19.374 --> 00:08:22.992
<i>(Police radio) suspect last seen
near Seventh Street and Santa Fe.</i>

67
00:08:23.211 --> 00:08:26.294
<i>(Radio) ...they have not let up at all.</i>

68
00:08:26.464 --> 00:08:31.004
<i>(Radio) All of a sudden, the Clippers
are grabbing all the rebounds.</i>

69
00:08:32.554 --> 00:08:35.763
<i>(Radio) The Clippers have a chance
to take the lead.</i>

70
00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:39.724
<i>(Radio) The fans are loving it.
They're on their feet.</i>

71
00:08:39.853 --> 00:08:42.850
<i>(Radio) He breaks it up.
Last four possessions,</i>

72
00:08:42.874 --> 00:08:45.644
<i>they've gone to Blake
Griffin on the block.</i>

73
00:08:45.942 --> 00:08:47.979
<i>(Radio) Less than a minute to play...</i>

74
00:08:49.988 --> 00:08:52.855
<i>(Police radio) Dispatch, this is 1-Adam-6.</i>

75
00:08:53.074 --> 00:08:56.317
<i>(Police radio) Possible suspect
vehicle sighted at stop light. Stand by.</i>

76
00:08:57.412 --> 00:08:59.073
<i>(Police radio) Roger, Unit 6.</i>

77
00:09:06.713 --> 00:09:08.704
(Engine revs, siren wails)

78
00:09:09.924 --> 00:09:12.336
(Tires screech)

79
00:09:27.984 --> 00:09:32.228
<i>(Radio) Inbound to Baylis, takes a shot.
Blocked by Griffin! It's not gonna go!</i>

80
00:09:32.447 --> 00:09:35.235
<i>(Radio) Griffin gets the rebound.
Time winding down.</i>

81
00:09:35.366 --> 00:09:40.611
<i>(Radio) Four, three,
two, (Radio) one...</i>

82
00:09:40.747 --> 00:09:43.705
<i>(Radio) The Los Angeles Clippers win
the ball game...</i>

83
00:09:52.759 --> 00:09:55.126
(Shouting and cheering)

84
00:10:06.773 --> 00:10:08.764
(Police siren)

85
00:13:10.373 --> 00:13:12.410
(Lift bell rings)

86
00:13:15.753 --> 00:13:18.165
- What floor?
- Fourth. Thanks.

87
00:13:30.685 --> 00:13:32.847
(Bell rings)

88
00:14:02.258 --> 00:14:04.920
Hey, kid. You know what?

89
00:14:09.515 --> 00:14:12.803
The director wants to see a roll over.
Are you OK with that?

90
00:14:13.019 --> 00:14:17.263
If you don't feel good, just abort
the shot. There's no shame in that.

91
00:14:17.523 --> 00:14:21.687
You're doubling for the star.
You're not like a day player or anything.

92
00:14:21.903 --> 00:14:24.065
And I got you 500 more, huh?

93
00:14:24.280 --> 00:14:27.568
Of course, we split that.
Are you OK? Ready to go?

94
00:14:27.742 --> 00:14:29.779
All right. Counting on you!

95
00:14:44.592 --> 00:14:46.754
<i>Excuse me, pal. You're new here.</i>

96
00:14:46.969 --> 00:14:50.007
<i>Before I put you on camera,
you sign this contract.</i>

97
00:14:50.139 --> 00:14:52.506
It releases liability to the company

98
00:14:52.725 --> 00:14:55.683
in case you die, get maimed
or seriously injured.

99
00:14:55.812 --> 00:14:58.429
- And... action!
- All right, kid.

100
00:15:05.613 --> 00:15:07.604
All right, that's a cut!

101
00:15:07.782 --> 00:15:10.865
Oh, kid, that was fantastic!
Just fantastic!

102
00:15:11.077 --> 00:15:15.617
OK. How you doin'? Are you all right?
You were good. That was perfect.

103
00:16:11.804 --> 00:16:14.011
<i>- You're a monkey.
- You're the monkey.</i>

104
00:16:14.265 --> 00:16:16.632
<i>- You're the monkey.
- You're the monkey.</i>

105
00:16:16.767 --> 00:16:18.804
Hey, tell me one thing.

106
00:16:18.978 --> 00:16:20.889
- I love you.
- I love you.

107
00:17:16.202 --> 00:17:19.490
- Where should I put this?
- In the kitchen. Thank you.

108
00:17:21.541 --> 00:17:23.578
Just be a second.

109
00:17:34.178 --> 00:17:36.215
- Scary.
- (Boy laughs)

110
00:17:39.183 --> 00:17:41.800
Hey, you want a toothpick?

111
00:17:47.608 --> 00:17:50.441
- You want a glass of water?
- OK.

112
00:18:01.747 --> 00:18:03.203
Thanks.

113
00:18:07.128 --> 00:18:09.165
So you just moved to LA?

114
00:18:10.673 --> 00:18:12.755
No, I've been here for a while.

115
00:18:13.843 --> 00:18:16.084
- You're just new here?
- Mm-hm.

116
00:18:22.143 --> 00:18:24.180
That's Benicio's father.

117
00:18:25.521 --> 00:18:27.512
Where is he?

118
00:18:28.649 --> 00:18:30.640
He's in prison.

119
00:18:31.736 --> 00:18:33.226
Oh.

120
00:18:33.404 --> 00:18:35.486
What do you do?

121
00:18:37.575 --> 00:18:39.532
I drive.

122
00:18:40.911 --> 00:18:43.448
Like a limo driver?

123
00:18:43.664 --> 00:18:45.951
- No, like for movies.
- Oh.

124
00:18:47.918 --> 00:18:50.751
You mean all the car chases and stuff?

125
00:18:50.963 --> 00:18:52.044
Yeah.

126
00:18:53.174 --> 00:18:55.711
Isn't that dangerous?

127
00:19:04.560 --> 00:19:07.052
It's only part-time.

128
00:19:07.313 --> 00:19:09.350
Mostly I work at a garage.

129
00:19:09.607 --> 00:19:12.190
- Where?
- Reseda Boulevard.

130
00:19:21.327 --> 00:19:23.284
I gotta go.

131
00:19:24.664 --> 00:19:26.154
OK.

132
00:19:28.250 --> 00:19:30.537
- Thanks for the water.
- Say "bye".

133
00:19:30.753 --> 00:19:32.744
(BENICIO) Bye!

134
00:20:09.875 --> 00:20:12.458
<i>- Mr Rose, your food, sir.
- OK.</i>

135
00:20:12.670 --> 00:20:16.334
<i>Chicken chow mein
and some Peking duck.</i>

136
00:20:16.465 --> 00:20:18.581
Where are the chopsticks?

137
00:20:18.801 --> 00:20:21.964
- You know, the guy just...
- Go get 'em. Go get 'em.

138
00:20:22.096 --> 00:20:25.054
I don't want that. I don't want that.
You eat it.

139
00:20:25.182 --> 00:20:27.514
Chopsticks and a fortune cookie.

140
00:20:27.727 --> 00:20:30.579
Put out the fuckin'
cigarette! I'm eating.

141
00:20:30.603 --> 00:20:31.603
Sorry.

142
00:20:31.689 --> 00:20:34.852
- What's the matter with you?
- I'm just...

143
00:20:34.984 --> 00:20:37.817
What happened to all the ashtrays
in this town?

144
00:20:37.945 --> 00:20:41.654
You run a good business.
I don't know why you want to change.

145
00:20:41.782 --> 00:20:46.367
You know how much my business made
last year? 30 grand.

146
00:20:46.579 --> 00:20:48.695
I can build a car in six months

147
00:20:48.914 --> 00:20:51.997
and in six seconds,
these jerks write it off as a stunt

148
00:20:52.209 --> 00:20:54.450
that won't even make it into the movie.

149
00:20:54.670 --> 00:20:58.789
See, all I need is a hard used stock car.
That's all.

150
00:20:59.008 --> 00:21:02.842
I figure we start off with small
town circuit and work our way up.

151
00:21:02.970 --> 00:21:05.928
Once we get to the show,
we're talking millions.

152
00:21:06.140 --> 00:21:08.757
- The chopsticks, sir.
- Where's the cookies?

153
00:21:08.893 --> 00:21:12.056
- Uh...
- Forget it. Forget it.

154
00:21:12.188 --> 00:21:15.601
- So you still haven't given me a number.
- All right.

155
00:21:16.692 --> 00:21:18.729
430,000 dollars.

156
00:21:18.861 --> 00:21:20.317
Oh...

157
00:21:20.529 --> 00:21:24.648
Mr Rose, I wouldn't come to you
unless I was absolutely sure about it.

158
00:21:24.867 --> 00:21:26.904
How can you be sure, Shannon?

159
00:21:27.036 --> 00:21:31.246
What do you got
that the big professional race teams don't?

160
00:21:32.416 --> 00:21:36.284
- I got the driver.
- You said they had half a dozen drivers.

161
00:21:36.504 --> 00:21:39.667
Not like this one. This kid is special.

162
00:21:39.882 --> 00:21:44.001
Been working with him for a while.
I've never seen anything like it.

163
00:21:44.220 --> 00:21:48.214
- If I had the money, I'd back him myself.
- Yeah, but you don't.

164
00:21:49.350 --> 00:21:55.141
Mr Rose, you put this kid behind the wheel,
there's nothing he can't do.

165
00:21:55.272 --> 00:21:58.390
There's money here. You can't lose.

166
00:21:58.609 --> 00:22:01.271
Fuck you eating Chink food
in my restaurant?

167
00:22:01.403 --> 00:22:03.986
What's a Jew doing running a pizzeria?

168
00:22:04.114 --> 00:22:06.856
You remember Shannon.

169
00:22:09.829 --> 00:22:12.821
Take a fuckin' hike!
I want to talk to my partner.

170
00:22:15.376 --> 00:22:17.458
I'm just fuckin' with you.

171
00:22:17.670 --> 00:22:20.537
How you doin', Shannon?
How's the fuckin' leg?

172
00:22:20.673 --> 00:22:23.586
I paid my debt.

173
00:22:24.677 --> 00:22:27.419
I'll think about it. OK?

174
00:22:27.638 --> 00:22:29.675
But I want to meet the kid first.

175
00:22:29.807 --> 00:22:32.299
That's all I ask.

176
00:22:44.572 --> 00:22:46.779
I want you to meet somebody.

177
00:22:46.991 --> 00:22:51.110
Don't say what you like about the car.
I want to drive the price down.

178
00:22:51.328 --> 00:22:53.695
Kid, I want you to meet Mr Bernie Rose.

179
00:22:54.582 --> 00:22:56.493
Nice to meet you.

180
00:23:01.714 --> 00:23:03.751
My hands are a little dirty.

181
00:23:03.883 --> 00:23:06.466
So are mine.

182
00:23:10.514 --> 00:23:13.097
Good driving out there.

183
00:23:13.309 --> 00:23:14.549
Thanks.

184
00:23:17.062 --> 00:23:20.851
He's a good kid. So what do you think?
Do we get the 400?

185
00:23:22.401 --> 00:23:24.938
I'll give you 300 for 70%.

186
00:23:27.948 --> 00:23:29.438
Done.

187
00:23:31.285 --> 00:23:33.117
Right. Good.

188
00:23:33.329 --> 00:23:35.661
(Laughs) You won't be sorry!

189
00:23:41.503 --> 00:23:43.540
- I'm Shannon.
- Hi, I'm Irene.

190
00:23:43.756 --> 00:23:46.168
- How can I help you?
- It just broke down.

191
00:23:46.383 --> 00:23:49.466
- Just like that? Want me to take a look?
- Yes, please.

192
00:23:49.678 --> 00:23:53.171
All right. Uh... We got all our bays full.

193
00:23:53.390 --> 00:23:56.974
Hey, pal, just drop it down here.
We'll push it in, all right?

194
00:23:57.186 --> 00:23:59.393
We want to push her in to number three.

195
00:23:59.605 --> 00:24:01.721
- The car, not you.
- Oh, good.

196
00:24:01.941 --> 00:24:03.557
- Hi.
- Hi.

197
00:24:04.985 --> 00:24:07.477
- Ah, you two know each other?
- Don't.

198
00:24:07.696 --> 00:24:10.108
- Oh, look at that.
- We're neighbors.

199
00:24:10.324 --> 00:24:14.113
Neighbors? Very good.
We'll try to be neighborly, too.

200
00:24:34.264 --> 00:24:36.676
- You blinked.
- What?

201
00:24:37.768 --> 00:24:40.931
- Can I call a cab from here?
- Yeah, sure.

202
00:24:42.022 --> 00:24:45.936
What am I talking about?
You and the kid are neighbors, right?

203
00:24:46.151 --> 00:24:48.609
- He can take you home.
- No, I'd feel bad.

204
00:24:48.821 --> 00:24:53.987
No, don't even think twice about it.
He'd be happy to do it. He's a good guy.

205
00:24:55.244 --> 00:24:58.407
He walked into my shop here
five or six years ago.

206
00:24:59.456 --> 00:25:02.323
Right out of the blue, asking for a job.

207
00:25:02.543 --> 00:25:05.911
So I put him to the test
to see what he could do.

208
00:25:06.130 --> 00:25:08.292
- The kid's amazing.
- Yeah.

209
00:25:08.507 --> 00:25:10.874
Sol hire him on the spot - boom!

210
00:25:11.093 --> 00:25:14.677
At about half the wages I normally pay.
He didn't blink an eye.

211
00:25:15.764 --> 00:25:18.722
Hey, kid!
Come over here for a second, will you?

212
00:25:18.934 --> 00:25:21.471
And I have been exploiting him ever since.

213
00:25:21.687 --> 00:25:23.519
(Both laugh)

214
00:25:23.731 --> 00:25:25.563
Ssh, don't tell him.

215
00:25:25.691 --> 00:25:29.309
It looks like we have a bigger problem
than I thought.

216
00:25:29.528 --> 00:25:32.611
We're going to have to keep the car here
for a few days.

217
00:25:32.823 --> 00:25:36.441
So I offered your services
to take BENICIO and Irene home.

218
00:25:36.660 --> 00:25:38.697
Would that be OK?

219
00:25:40.956 --> 00:25:43.197
- Yeah, sure.
- Yeah.

220
00:25:45.335 --> 00:25:47.997
I don't have wheels... on my car.

221
00:25:48.130 --> 00:25:49.211
OK.

222
00:25:49.423 --> 00:25:52.586
- It's one thing you should know about me.
- Put the tires on.

223
00:25:52.801 --> 00:25:54.838
- You got five minutes?
- Yeah.

224
00:26:17.826 --> 00:26:20.363
Hey, do you want to see something?

225
00:26:22.998 --> 00:26:24.705
Yeah.

226
00:26:27.628 --> 00:26:29.118
OK.

227
00:28:24.411 --> 00:28:26.618
That was good.

228
00:28:26.830 --> 00:28:28.867
He had a good time.

229
00:28:37.090 --> 00:28:39.081
Me, too.

230
00:28:45.182 --> 00:28:48.265
Sorry if I put you on the spot
showing up like that.

231
00:28:48.477 --> 00:28:50.514
It's OK.

232
00:29:13.418 --> 00:29:15.876
I'm not doing anything this weekend.

233
00:29:20.300 --> 00:29:22.541
If you want a ride or something.

234
00:30:02.175 --> 00:30:04.542
(BENICIO giggles)

235
00:30:57.189 --> 00:31:01.808
<i>Don't worry about her bumps and bruises.
Fiberglass is easily replaceable.</i>

236
00:31:01.943 --> 00:31:04.901
Put a coat of paint on there,
