- It's over there.

494
01:05:04.651 --> 01:05:06.858
Aargh! Aaargh!

495
01:05:07.070 --> 01:05:08.606
<i>Ram!</i>

496
01:05:20.625 --> 01:05:23.617
Whose money do I have?

497
01:05:23.753 --> 01:05:26.085
Don't worry. They're gonna come get it.

498
01:05:26.214 --> 01:05:28.000
No, no...!

499
01:05:28.258 --> 01:05:31.922
- Call them.
- Somebody call Nino!

500
01:05:42.939 --> 01:05:45.897
Do you remember this?

501
01:05:51.364 --> 01:05:52.820
(Gags)

502
01:06:04.461 --> 01:06:06.498
(Phone ringing)

503
01:06:08.798 --> 01:06:10.539
<i>Hello?</i>

504
01:06:10.758 --> 01:06:12.499
Nino?

505
01:06:12.719 --> 01:06:16.838
<i>No, sorry, pal. Why don't you
call back later? We're closed.</i>

506
01:06:17.015 --> 01:06:20.849
I think Nino would be upset
that you made him wait.

507
01:06:20.935 --> 01:06:23.427
<i>Can I ask what this is about?</i>

508
01:06:23.688 --> 01:06:27.397
- I have something of his.
<i>- And that would be?</i>

509
01:06:27.525 --> 01:06:29.641
A million dollars.

510
01:06:31.279 --> 01:06:33.361
<i>Please hold.</i>

511
01:06:39.662 --> 01:06:44.452
<i>(Nino) You got something
that fucking belongs to me?</i>

512
01:06:47.837 --> 01:06:50.044
It seems that way.

513
01:06:51.799 --> 01:06:54.166
And you're calling me?

514
01:06:55.261 --> 01:06:57.047
Why?

515
01:06:57.263 --> 01:06:59.880
You expect me to buy my own shit back?

516
01:07:00.141 --> 01:07:02.348
<i>I'm not selling it.</i>

517
01:07:02.477 --> 01:07:07.597
I'm going to give you a time and a place
and you'll come and get it. Understand?

518
01:07:09.025 --> 01:07:11.642
<i>And what do you get out of it?</i>

519
01:07:12.737 --> 01:07:15.695
Just that. Out of it.

520
01:07:16.783 --> 01:07:19.400
<i>And your partners are happy with that?</i>

521
01:07:21.162 --> 01:07:23.449
I don't have any partners.

522
01:07:24.499 --> 01:07:27.912
You discuss this with anybody else?

523
01:07:29.295 --> 01:07:31.332
<i>No, just you.</i>

524
01:07:32.465 --> 01:07:35.002
You're not very good at this, are you?

525
01:07:37.679 --> 01:07:39.545
(Hangs up)

526
01:07:46.187 --> 01:07:48.804
Go check out who this fucking guy is.

527
01:08:09.752 --> 01:08:11.789
(Knock at door)

528
01:08:27.145 --> 01:08:29.728
Can I talk to you for a minute?

529
01:08:31.024 --> 01:08:33.482
Can't talk. I have to go.

530
01:08:35.653 --> 01:08:38.315
Can I just walk with you for...?

531
01:08:38.531 --> 01:08:40.147
Yeah.

532
01:08:59.135 --> 01:09:01.593
I have to tell you something.

533
01:09:07.685 --> 01:09:10.143
Standard was into some...

534
01:09:11.439 --> 01:09:14.056
guys in prison for a lot of money.

535
01:09:16.653 --> 01:09:20.772
And they were going to hurt you
and BENICIO if he didn't pay it.

536
01:09:23.117 --> 01:09:25.700
He asked me for my help.

537
01:09:28.539 --> 01:09:30.997
Everything went wrong.

538
01:09:34.170 --> 01:09:36.161
I'm sorry.

539
01:09:40.593 --> 01:09:42.800
I've still got the money.

540
01:09:46.891 --> 01:09:49.474
You could have it if you wanted to.

541
01:09:51.062 --> 01:09:53.474
You could take BENICIO and...

542
01:10:05.243 --> 01:10:08.952
I just thought
you could get out of here if you wanted.

543
01:10:11.499 --> 01:10:13.740
I could come with you.

544
01:10:17.547 --> 01:10:19.788
I could look out for you.

545
01:10:20.007 --> 01:10:22.044
(Door opens)

546
01:10:24.095 --> 01:10:25.756
Sorry.

547
01:10:25.972 --> 01:10:27.963
Wrong floor.

548
01:13:50.468 --> 01:13:53.005
They came to my apartment, Shannon.

549
01:13:54.096 --> 01:13:56.258
How do they know where I live?

550
01:13:58.643 --> 01:14:02.728
I told you I was gonna call Bernie.
I just wanted him to know

551
01:14:02.939 --> 01:14:07.649
that you're not interested in the money.
That you just did it for the girl.

552
01:14:07.777 --> 01:14:10.394
What did you say?

553
01:14:12.281 --> 01:14:15.319
- What did you fucking say about Irene?
- Calm down!

554
01:14:15.534 --> 01:14:19.653
- You told them about Irene!
- Calm down, kid! Calm down.

555
01:14:19.872 --> 01:14:24.617
- I should fucking kill you!
- Listen, I just wanted him to know

556
01:14:24.835 --> 01:14:29.375
that as soon as you returned the money,
that was the end of it. That's all.

557
01:14:29.590 --> 01:14:32.252
How was I supposed to know that?!

558
01:14:32.468 --> 01:14:35.130
OK? Let me just talk to Bernie.

559
01:14:35.346 --> 01:14:39.465
- OK?
- Why have you got to fuck everything up?

560
01:14:39.684 --> 01:14:43.803
How was I supposed to know
everything led to Nino?!

561
01:14:48.234 --> 01:14:52.774
They're going to come looking for me
and they're going to come for you.

562
01:14:52.989 --> 01:14:55.026
Do you understand?

563
01:14:55.241 --> 01:14:58.734
You gotta get out of here
and you gotta get out now.

564
01:14:58.953 --> 01:15:01.820
- Listen to me, Shannon.
- Oh, God...

565
01:15:02.039 --> 01:15:06.579
Listen. You get out of here
and you never fucking come back.

566
01:15:07.670 --> 01:15:09.707
You never come back.

567
01:15:15.136 --> 01:15:17.468
What are you gonna do?

568
01:15:33.904 --> 01:15:36.362
I already gave you my advice.

569
01:15:36.574 --> 01:15:40.033
You should have taken the money
and left the guy alone.

570
01:15:40.244 --> 01:15:44.579
- It's not that simple, Bernie.
- Not now it's bounced up in your face!

571
01:15:44.790 --> 01:15:47.452
I owe you this guy. I'll get rid of him.

572
01:15:47.585 --> 01:15:52.036
Shut the fuck up,
you fucking monkey.

573
01:15:52.256 --> 01:15:56.375
The money belongs to some half-assed
wiseguy out of Philly.

574
01:15:56.594 --> 01:16:00.713
I got tipped off he was stashing
a million bucks in a pawn shop.

575
01:16:00.931 --> 01:16:03.889
He was gonna set up a rival operation.

576
01:16:04.018 --> 01:16:06.760
So you stole from the East Coast mob?

577
01:16:06.979 --> 01:16:12.440
No, I stole from some jumped-up punk
who was trying to step on our action.

578
01:16:12.568 --> 01:16:17.062
Then why didn't you come to me
before you set up this dummy robbery?

579
01:16:17.281 --> 01:16:21.240
- Before you hire this piece of shit.
- This is off to the side.

580
01:16:21.368 --> 01:16:25.453
- I didn't want to involve you.
- Well, I'm involved now!

581
01:16:26.540 --> 01:16:28.781
I'm gonna tell you something.

582
01:16:29.001 --> 01:16:30.742
Anybody,

583
01:16:30.961 --> 01:16:36.297
anybody finds out you stole
from the family, we're both dead.

584
01:16:36.425 --> 01:16:38.837
What fucking family?!

585
01:16:39.053 --> 01:16:41.841
The family who still
calls me a fuckin' kike?

586
01:16:42.056 --> 01:16:43.967
To my face!

587
01:16:45.434 --> 01:16:50.554
I'm 59 years old, Bernie! They still
pinch my cheek like I'm some fucking kid!

588
01:16:52.108 --> 01:16:56.193
- Family.
- The money always flows up, Izzy.

589
01:16:56.403 --> 01:16:58.815
You know that.

590
01:16:58.948 --> 01:17:01.781
That's why this driver's gotta go, Bernie.

591
01:17:02.868 --> 01:17:06.202
Gotta go. And your pal, Shannon.

592
01:17:06.330 --> 01:17:10.824
These are the only two guys
who can tie me to this robbery.

593
01:17:30.020 --> 01:17:33.433
Aaaargh!

594
01:17:49.123 --> 01:17:52.036
Now it's your turn to clean up after me.

595
01:18:55.356 --> 01:18:57.893
All these priceless cars.

596
01:18:58.108 --> 01:19:00.770
One would think you'd have better locks.

597
01:19:02.821 --> 01:19:08.112
- My door's always open to you.
- Going somewhere?

598
01:19:09.245 --> 01:19:10.861
Ah...

599
01:19:13.249 --> 01:19:18.244
- Thinking about it.
- I'm looking for your driver.

600
01:19:20.381 --> 01:19:23.169
You break in here, I figure it's bad news.

601
01:19:23.300 --> 01:19:25.883
No, Shannon. It's bad luck.

602
01:19:27.263 --> 01:19:32.975
Two thousand heists a year in this city,
he has to pick the wrong one.

603
01:19:33.102 --> 01:19:37.812
- He tried to put it right.
- He picked the wrong guy for that, too.

604
01:19:38.023 --> 01:19:42.483
My partner is a belligerent asshole
with his back against the wall.

605
01:19:42.611 --> 01:19:44.568
Right now, so am I.

606
01:19:45.656 --> 01:19:48.444
If I don't set this
straight, I'm in big trouble.

607
01:19:51.245 --> 01:19:53.907
Any idea where he might be?

608
01:19:56.458 --> 01:19:58.290
Mexico.

609
01:19:58.502 --> 01:20:01.460
Or maybe it was Belize.

610
01:20:04.800 --> 01:20:06.882
Really?

611
01:20:12.641 --> 01:20:15.474
I was getting excited
about this whole thing.

612
01:20:15.686 --> 01:20:17.927
My name on a car!

613
01:20:18.147 --> 01:20:21.139
I mean, look how beautiful!

614
01:20:21.275 --> 01:20:23.858
I wanted to see my name on this thing.

615
01:20:25.404 --> 01:20:29.523
I think we would have
made a go at this business.

616
01:20:44.089 --> 01:20:47.207
- Ah!
- Don't worry. Don't worry, that's it.

617
01:20:47.343 --> 01:20:51.587
It's done. There's no pain.
It's over, it's over.

618
01:25:21.199 --> 01:25:23.315
(Engine revs)

619
01:25:29.458 --> 01:25:31.870
What the fuck was that?

620
01:26:03.950 --> 01:26:06.817
- Let's get outta here.
- Yeah.

621
01:26:09.498 --> 01:26:11.535
(Engine revs)

622
01:26:32.854 --> 01:26:34.811
(Door alarm pings)

623
01:26:46.868 --> 01:26:48.825
(Breathes heavily)

624
01:28:08.658 --> 01:28:10.695
<i>(Bernie) Hello?</i>

625
01:28:10.911 --> 01:28:15.451
You know the story
about the scorpion and the frog?

626
01:28:17.209 --> 01:28:21.328
Your friend Nino didn't make it
across the river.

627
01:28:22.422 --> 01:28:25.210
<i>I think this has gone on long enough.</i>

628
01:28:26.551 --> 01:28:29.418
You see any reason for it to continue?

629
01:28:30.514 --> 01:28:32.972
What do you say we meet?

630
01:28:35.352 --> 01:28:37.093
<i>Why?</i>

631
01:28:38.688 --> 01:28:43.649
Well, you, me and your girlfriend
are the only players left.

632
01:28:43.860 --> 01:28:46.318
How's that for a reason?

633
01:28:48.490 --> 01:28:50.106
When?

634
01:28:50.325 --> 01:28:54.114
<i>Tomorrow.
There's a place on Sherman Way.</i>

635
01:28:54.329 --> 01:28:58.448
<i>It's a restaurant called The Great Wall.
Do you know it?</i>

636
01:29:25.819 --> 01:29:28.277
<i>(Driver) Can I talk to you?</i>

637
01:29:29.781 --> 01:29:32.239
<i>I won't keep you long.</i>

638
01:29:37.080 --> 01:29:41.620
<i>I have to go somewhere
and I don't think I can come back.</i>

639
01:29:45.213 --> 01:29:47.671
<i>But I just wanted you to know</i>

640
01:29:47.883 --> 01:29:50.545
<i>getting to be around you and BENICIO,</i>

641
01:29:52.679 --> 01:29:56.172
<i>it was the best thing
that ever happened to me.</i>

642
01:30:47.567 --> 01:30:50.434
Did you bring the money?

643
01:30:55.700 --> 01:30:58.237
Here's what I'm prepared to offer.

644
01:30:58.453 --> 01:31:01.070
You give me the money, the girl is safe.

645
01:31:01.289 --> 01:31:05.408
Forever. Nobody knows about her.
She's off the map.

646
01:31:06.962 --> 01:31:09.545
I can't offer you the same.

647
01:31:10.465 --> 01:31:12.923
So this is what I would suggest.

648
01:31:13.134 --> 01:31:16.001
We conclude our deal, we'll shake hands.

649
01:31:16.221 --> 01:31:18.838
You start the rest of your life.

650
01:31:21.476 --> 01:31:25.845
Any dreams you have,
or plans, or hopes for your future,

651
01:31:26.064 --> 01:31:29.557
I think you're gonna have to
put that on hold.

652
01:31:29.776 --> 01:31:33.485
For the rest of your life,
you'll be looking over your shoulder.

653
01:31:33.697 --> 01:31:38.032
I'm just telling you this
because I want you to know the truth.

654
01:31:38.243 --> 01:31:40.280
But the girl is safe.

655
01:32:00.557 --> 01:32:02.889
Where's the money now?

656
01:32:03.018 --> 01:32:05.009
It's in the car.

657
01:32:13.445 --> 01:32:15.277
Come on.

658
01:32:21.828 --> 01:32:23.569
Ungh!

